CONGRESS of the People has condemns the death threats made against
the Director General in the Presidency Phindile Baleni. The Presidency on Saturday that they have referred the
threat to security agencies. COPE National Spokesperson Dennis Bloem said in their statement,
“We know it is not the first time that these thieves are using this dirty
tricks to intimidate and insult. They used the same tactics against the
Chairperson of the Zondo Commission, Chief Justice Raymond Zondo, in an attempt
for him to stop the Commission.” “These thieves must not think that they will turn our
country into a Banana Republic. Some of us will never allow it. We must warn
these thieves and tell them, that we are prepared to fight them the same way we
fought the apartheid criminals who were hell bent in terrorising us.” He said they are calling upon State Security Agency, Hawks
and the entire law enforcement agencies to track down these thieves and deal
very harshly with them. READ: BULLET threat for DG in the Presidency! President's spokesman Vincent Magwenya said, "The Director-General reported this matter to security agencies and she is receiving protection to enable her to continue her critical duties as Director-General of the Presidency, Cabinet Secretary and convenor of the Forum of South African Directors-General."